flowRoot.flowPara: I am a proud member of the design school known as What The Hell Were You Thinking.

The plan is to set ids for each Inkscape layer, HTML areas, canvas clip path and each animated object. Then use CanvasNode's getElementById to grab the objects, and script animations and event listeners.

And create some sort of layer system using several canvases to minimize the amount of redraw. Limiting redraw to the bounding boxes of the changed objects might be nice too. But, get the basics working first.
The goal is an accessible HTML page that degrades gracefully and cranks up the fireworks on modern browsers. Or rather, the tools and experience gained from building one.
